h3.div: The South-Western City School District will continue distributing food during the extended closure. The meals will be "Grab-n-Go" style. Children between the age of 1 and 18 will be able to pick up lunches and a breakfasts.

We’ve listened to our families and their needs so our distribution schedule will be changing for the remainder of the school year. Starting on Monday, April 27, we will be distributing multiple meals to children on Mondays and Wednesdays ONLY from 11:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m. at our current 15 school locations and an additional 16 school bus sites. On Mondays, children will receive two breakfasts and two lunches. On Wednesdays, children will receive three breakfasts and three lunches.
Children may pick up food from any one of the sites listed below Monday and Wednesday from 11:00 a.m. - 1:00 p.m.

p.strong: Note: The Mid-Ohio Food Bank will continue to provide prepackaged dinners FOR PICK UP ONLY at Westland High School, 146 Galloway Road, Galloway, on Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays from 3:30-4:30 p.m. until further notice. On Fridays ONLY - in addition to prepackaged dinners, families can receive a bag of groceries and fresh produce for the weekend.
